ANC veteran Winnie Madikizela-Mandela was admitted to the Milpark Hospital in Johannesburg on Thursday night. Madikizela-Mandela’s spokesperson, Victor Dlamini, said she had been admitted for a routine check-up and was kept for additional observation‚ according to reports. In December last year‚ Madikizela-Mandela‚ 80‚ was rushed to hospital for reasons not made known to the public. In April last year she spent some time in hospital following back surgery. TMG Digital